rComments: He talks slowly and takes big pauses between his sentences, like full minute pauses, so watch WebOption at 2x speed if you can. It'll save you a lot of time. He seems like a nice guy and has a nice accent.
Straightforward course, read lectures, attempt to get a 100 on modules and make good notes and you will get a food mark for sure.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lecture heavy', 'Get ready to read', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: I have no idea why he uses those modules. The module questions are totally not about geology. They are like IELTS readings. Even a person who doesn't know anything about geology would do these modules. Also, the questions are tough to understand and not clearly stated. I will not take any courses associated with him.

Nick was a great and interesting professor who really cared about his students. He devoted time before every lecture to speak to students outside of the lecture hall, replied almost instantly to emails, and had many office hours that likely no students used. His videos, textbooks and words were very inspirational and uplifting. Great Job!
Does not bother to make his lectures interesting, which makes it difficult for students to study for such a heavy-content-based course.
This is by far the easiest course to take in UTSC. Nice and easy 4.0, just got to watch the lectures and take good notes, there is no need to by the textbook or even read it.

Definitely not a bird course. Cr/ncr for the nat sci br. Very difficult to take notes, lectures go on tangent ALL THE TIME. There's 10 modules 1 per week, those are very annoying to do and difficult even when you do it carefully, which again shows it's not bird. Really dislike the course, if u don't like geo, u won't like this course.
Really great prof, a respected and charismatic man. Loved watching his lectures and following him on his adventures. Exams are fair and there is huge potential to get an A in this course.

Attending his lectures, memorizing key terms and doing the assignments you will pass. May be the best prof I have had. Really loves geology, presents it in an entertaining way. Has somewhat of a stand up comedian's ability. The world would not have problems if all men were like him. Hope to be like him one day. Careful when he loses his temper

He is TERRIBLE! Can you believe it, professor in environmental science who doesn't believe in climate change and loves Trump. And if we leave his personal opinions out of this, his lectures are absoultely random. I came out of it feeling that I learnt nothing at all. Because he doesn't actually teach you! Avoid him at all cost!!!

Prof. Eyles is a nice guy but the class was horrible. The lectures were so boring and dry... He was not engaging at all. Most people stopped going to class after the second lecture. The poster assignment was not as easy as everyone said either. Would NOT recommend this class as a bird course unless you are actually interested in geology.

Great prof! He gives sample questions before a midterm or final which usually tends to be the exact same questions on the midterm and final.. pay attention to what he says and you should be good! readings are very helpful not really necessary

His lectures are honestly really bad. There is no clear pattern to what he is teaching. He keeps going off in tangents about some topic while explain the main points which leaves the class very confused as to what he is trying to explain. The textbook which is required for the course is simply made up of facts squeezed into sentences and has no flo

He is a extremely BORING person. His lectures are so dry and random, it is really hard to actually learn anything from him because he is always ALL OVER THE PLACE. His slides are TERRIBLE! Like seriously, the most random stuff possible. He literally just puts pictures on without any text comments. Exam completely unrelated with lectures. pointless

His class was great and I learned a lot but the quizzes were SOOOO raaanddddoom!!! The marking for the presentation was also pretty mysterious but not to the point where it wasn't fair. The only thing that really disappointed me was finding out the the TA isn't single.... FML :,,(

You could tell Prof. Eyles really loves what he teaches. I found the way he clarified & simplified complex key concepts during lectures to be really helpful. While the syllabus may look intimidating, you only need to read a few main chapters to do well on the exams. I only wish the poster assignment (group project) wasn't worth as much as it was.

Didn't like him in A06, didn't like him in C21 either. His lecture slides has no content only picture as a background. He mumbles A LOT and only seems to say half of the definition all the time. He doesn't provide a conducive environment for students to learn. If you do take this course, just make sure you read Chp2 of his textbook, he wrote it btw

Pretty cool prof, his accent makes things easier to remember in my opinion. Midterm was fair, but our poster was marked unfairly in my opinion, but other than that it's a good gpa booster if you put in a bit of work. Text book is essential since his slides are all pictures. MAKE SURE you know the brand of his motorcycle for the test (BMW).
midterm was based on both lectures and textbook. lectures are super-boring. 100 MC q's for both midterm and final. poster assignment was fun and a mark booster !
I found it a bit difficult to pay attention in his lectures, because he was a boring lecturer. The class itself was interesting enough, and he was a nice person.

Amazing lecturer. He is there when you need him and he is very approachable. If you put in effort, you will see results. Just do the weekly readings and you will be fine. Attendance is not mandatory, but it is recommended cause he does make questions linked directly to the lectures. In overall, I would definitely take his class again.
Majority of the exam material comes from his lectures. His lectures are all pictures and he does the talking, therefore you need to go to class to write down what he says.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Lecture heavy', 'Group projects']

rComments: Professor Eyles reminded me of how much I enjoy the environmental sciences; I was only taking it as part of the breadth requirement, but now I wish I majored it. He makes his expectations clear, is extremely fair, and offers helpful advice during office hours. Overall, a great prof to deal with.

This course an an easy introduction to planet earth. As a Geo enthusiast I believe if you have taken a Geo class in high school or in the past, this course will be an easy A. Final exam was fair and easy if you apply yourself in lecture and skim over the readings in the chapter. I recommend going to each lecture and not relying on online webcast.

I have to admit, his lectures ARE boring. But if you really listen to Eyles, you can tell that he knows his stuff. He is an amazing professor, very understanding and passionate about teaching. Definitely take his class!
Midterm was canceled due the the TA strike which the grading was modified to 50% final and the other half final. Easy mark still.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: Lectures are very boring. Especially watching online for an hour and a half. Textbook chapters are long. 1 midterm, 1 final, 1 poster assignment (group project). Okay course.
simply awesome prof. really enjoyed his class
Awsome prof, guess kinda is his own textbook, great knowledge in the field of study! Explains very clearly, test are not easy, but he's a fun prof. Should also run for survivor!
Best prof ever! Recommend anyone to take his class, enjoyed it a lot. Now making it my specialist.

I'm taking the online lecture, and am very happy. The lectures are kinda dry, but sometimes he rushes through a few points I need to write down. So I pause him and write! :D But I feel bad for the real lecture people. The assignments are very fair. DO THE READINGS, and you'll do fine on the quizzes.

This prof is awesome, down to earth and always willing to help students.I like his teaching methods. There are online quizzes which are extremely important and helpful for the final exam. Makes the class pretty interesting. He's done a lot of field work which are amazing. I would definitely recommend anyone to take his class.
This prof is such a jerk, his exams have nothing to do with the lec. their arbitrary and random DONT TAKE THIS COURSE, you'll only regret it later.

Simply one of the greatest geology experts in the world. Knows his stuff and genuinely wants to teach. Great, easy going prof whose also down to earth. Always willing to help. An asset to U of T. Simply the best.     For prospective B15 students: TAKE THE COURSE! The field trip is very, very cool. And the hike is one that you'll never ever forget.
Great prof and extremely helpful with any questions presented to him.  Enjoyable class overall.  Good Job!!!

The course was really interesting and weekly quizzes really helped prepare for the final. The assignment topics were also interesting and it was marked generously. The professor had a nice way of teaching. Overall, it's the best class I took so far.

Prof. Eyles is really passionate about his work, and makes you enjoy learning about rocks, no matter how boring people think they are.  His field trips are extremely fun, a little dangerous, but fun and informative!
he's a nice teacher. the course was interesting and he taught it pretty well. and he's hot.
its a laughable course

He is kind of arrogant. Though he is full of knowlage, he is not quite willing to help outside class. If you ask him questions, he will think that you are stupid and he expects you to know all the stuff that is not printed in the textbook! The mid term is ok, but watch out for the final, i doubt anyone can finish that in 2 hours.
he is an very intelligent man, and he did help when approaching him.  It is true that his fieldtrip was time & $ consuming and he marked the assign very difficulthis midterm was excellent!
The lectures are boring... and he is not helpful when you approach him in person. The field trip is a waste of time and money!

Very nice prof, good sense of humour and easy to understand. The lectures can be a little dry at times.
No Comments
Lovely accent and really charming but course material can get really boring
FUNNY AND NICE

He's a good professor.  I had EESB15 (Earth History) and EESC31 (Glacial Sed.& Strat.) with him in 3rd year.  He LOVES fieldtrips, which is definitely the highlight of the course!  He knows his stuff, and if you read his text book you will be set.
